  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Boil a kettle, then slice</span> the <strong>seasonal squash</strong> in half and scoop out the seeds, discarding them</p>\n<p>Tip:<span class=\"text-highlight\"> for</span> easier chopping, use a bread <span class=\"text-highlight\">knife (oiling the knife helps too!)</span></p>\n<p>Note: our seasonal squashes will come in <span class=\"text-highlight\">all colours, shapes and sizes, but don't worry – the method will stay the same!</span></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice each <strong>squash</strong> <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>half</strong></span> into 1cm wedges</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>squash wedges</strong> to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 20-22 min or until softened with a slight bite</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, strip the<strong> sage leaves</strong> and chop them finely, discarding the stems</p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Add the <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>smoked streaky</strong></span> <strong>bacon</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until crisp, turning once halfway </p>\n<p>Once crisp, transfer it to a plate and set aside</p>\n<p>Reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>gnocchi </strong>to a pot of<strong> boiled water </strong>with a large pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Cook the<strong> gnocchi</strong> for 3 min or until it begins to rise to the top of the pot</p>\n<p>Once done, drain the <strong>gnocchi</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy cooking water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wipe the bacon pan clean with <strong>kitchen paper </strong>and return it to a medium heat</p>\n<p>Add 50g <span class=\"text-danger\">[100g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>chopped sage</strong> and cook for 2 min or until foaming and beginning to turn a light brown colour – this is your <strong>sage burnt butter</strong></p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, break the <strong>crispy <span class=\"text-highlight\">bacon</span></strong><span class=\"text-highlight\"> into s</span>hards (clean hands is the best way!)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained gnocchi </strong>to the <strong>sage burnt butter </strong>with the <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>squash wedges</strong> and <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>half</strong></span> the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p>\n<p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and a very generous grind of<strong> black pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>\n<p>Tip: add a small splash of <strong>starchy cooking water</strong> if the sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1802.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Wash the <strong>wild rocket</strong> and pat it dry</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Serve the<strong> squash &amp; sage gnocchi</strong> topped with the <strong>bacon shards</strong>,<strong> rocket </strong>and the <strong>remaining cheese</strong></span></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
